			<div class="content" id="post-content-1704352">
									

<p>That characterization comes across quite well in the story, art as defense/escape mechanism. It fits very well with the rest of the cast, as the whole exchange team seems to have one sort of borderline personality disorder or another.</p>
<p>It's just that Tyhja is supposed to have spent years on end training as an artist, seemingly to the exclusion of all else, even his napkin doodles would have a certain level of polish and technical proficiency. I have unfortunately frequent dealings with people trying to communicate their imagination to me in quick and dirty sketches, and there are elements that every trained artist uses without even realizing they are doing it. Even a ten second sketch of a T-rex on the back of a menu gets depth, shading, a logical shadow, etc.</p>

