<p>derp, there I go overlooking the easy way again.</p>
<p>But, y'know what? I take it all back anyway. Because the more I think about the different syles angle, the more it appeals to me. Antartica has a rigid, structured culture rooted in a genetically defined caste system. It only makes sense that the other aspects of their culture, such as art, would be similarly rigid and structured. Instead of focusing on realism (or deliberate rejection thereof) like our art tends to, their artists would be centered on making sure that it met all the technical rules of the approved and traditional style, whatever those might be. Making the picture look like what it is a picture of would be a secondary consideration, if that.</p>
<p>Don't need to thank me, I get almost as much entertainment out of commentary and trying to think up new wrinkles as I do out of reading in the first place.</p>

